{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> εὐκαιρ-ία</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> -ιη, ἡ, <b>good season, opportunity</b>, τὴν εὐ. διαφυλάττειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.34 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπολαύειν τῆς εὐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “D.” 3 “fragment” 89\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; εὐκαιρίαν ζητεῖν ἵνα.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Matt.26.16 \">NT</a>]; εὐ. τοῦ ἐλθεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PMich.” in “Class.Phil.” 22.250 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>leisure</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιστολαί” 17, 23; κατὰ πολλὴν εὐ. καὶ σχολήν 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 23 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]—a usage condemned by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc. and Suid. see at {σχολή}. \">Refs 9th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>appropriateness</b>, opposed to ἀκαιρία, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 272a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μεταφορᾶς, στίχων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.16b,736f. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>convenient situation</b>, τῶν πόλεων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 16.29.3, compare 4.44.11, 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.4. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>opportune supply</b>, ὑδάτων, of rainfall or irrigation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 3.23.4 (_plural_), 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 1.52. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>wealth, prosperity</b>, αἱ τῶν βίων εὐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.59.7, compare 13.9.2 (conj